\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{hyperref}
\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}
\title{Installing Python, Pygame, and other Packages on Windows}
\author{Geoffrey Matthews}
\begin{document}
\begin{description}
\item[Python]
  I like installing python using the Anaconda package, because you get
tons of important scientific packages automatically loaded.

\url{https://www.continuum.io/downloads}

\item[Packages]
  For installing packages on Windows, the most reliable method I've
  found is to use the unofficial binaries found here:

  \url{http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/}

  Packages you may want to consider:
  \begin{itemize}
  \item pygame
  \item pymunk
  \item box2d
  \item pyglet
  \end{itemize}
\end{description}

\end{document}

  
